(30, 16, 'Health Benefits of Some Fruits', 'health-benefits-of-some-fruits-7741', 'LoaevgtNslide3.jpg', 'SPINACH\r\n\r\ncommonly known as ALUGBATI  , grown as a backyard vegetables plants in the garden.\r\n\r\nYoruba name : Amunututu \r\n\r\nLike other green Vegetables, alugbati leaves are rich in iron and plenty of nutrition which is for useful health. \r\n\r\nHEALTH BENEFITS OF ALUGBATI LEAVES \r\n\r\nControl Blood Pressure \r\nAlugbati leaves are so powerful when it comes to controlling your blood pressure. Its high manganese and potassium content are beneficial for heart rate and blood pressure. These are the main reason why  it can prevent heart disease as well as able to relieve a headache related to high blood pressure \r\n\r\nPrevent Cancer\r\nLike other vegetables, alugbati is also packed with antioxidant , It fights free radicals , which is the main reason of some cancer. According to studies , green vegetables are excellent in preventing the growth of cancer cell in oral cavity and lungs.\r\n\r\nPrevent Constipation \r\nIts leaves are good for your digestive system . It aids bowel movement thus, preventing constipation and other related digestive problems.\r\n\r\nRelieve Ulcer \r\nThe smoothness of alugbati leaves is able to relieve stomach ulcer, It is healthy and safe for any digestive problems.\r\n\r\nGood for Pregnancy \r\nAlugbati leaves can provide folate, which is needed by pregnant women . It is essential for the babys nervous system.\r\n\r\nLose Weights \r\nEvery single serving of alugbati leaves contains many nutrients like natural fiber, vitamin and minerals, However it is very low in calorie. Its fiber content is also beneficial in improving your digestive organs, therefore, resulting to a good metabolism system which is the key to losing weight.\r\n\r\nRelease Toxins\r\nAs alugbati can improve bowel movement, it allows the body to release toxin from feces, Aside from this, its leaves are also known as a diuretic. It enables the body to release toxins through urine.\r\n\r\nPrevent Anemia \r\nAlso called as spinach, these leaves are also rich in iron. Its 100 grams of fresh leaves can fulfil  15%  of  your daily need of iron . Regular consumption of these can keep you from getting anemia .\r\n\r\nImprove Eyesight \r\nAlugbati leaves and its stem are rich in vitamin A , which is important for eyes health. Consumption of alugbati can, therefore, improve your eyesight.\r\n\r\nHelp You Sleep\r\nBesides maintaining the health of your skin and internal organs , alugbati can also help you relax. Magnesium and zinc present in alugbati,  help you close your eyes, relax your whole body and quickly recharge your energy .\r\n\r\nSoften Skin\r\nIf you want to have a soft skin , apply alugbati leaves on your skin and use it as a facial mask. It re-hydrates and cools down your skin.\r\n\r\nAnti-Aging Property \r\nAside from cancer, free radicals also cause premature aging. Prevent this by applying alugbati leaves to your skin . It has antioxidants that slow down the aging process and also makes your skin look younger.\r\n\r\nReduce Swelling \r\nThe leaves ability in cooling down skin is beneficial in reducing swelling. Its vitamin content blocks inflammation and reduces swelling.\r\n\r\nBoost Immunity \r\nVarious studies reveal that alugbati are high in vitamin C . Which is very good in improving the immune system.\r\n\r\nRecommendation In Consuming Alugbati Leaves \r\nMake sure to choose fresh , shiny leaves and firm stems. Avoid those sunken or discolored  and dry leaves. Before cooking, wash the \r\nalugbati leaves in cold running water . This vegetable is good to include into soup, stir-fry, or stew.', 'watermark-gJl2XATutapis.png', 1, '2022-08-11 14:42:43', '2022-08-11 14:19:49'),
